sentence: Looking at options trading activity among components of the Russell 3000 index, there is noteworthy activity today in Zumiez Inc (Symbol: ZUMZ), where a total volume of 4,810 contracts has been traded thus far today, a contract volume which is representative of approximately 481,000 underlying shares (given that every 1 contract represents 100 underlying shares).
That number works out to 108.4% of ZUMZ's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 443,670 shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $17.50 strike put option expiring August 19, 2016 , with 3,700 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 370,000 underlying shares of ZUMZ.

Vulcan Materials Co (Symbol: VMC) options are showing a volume of 8,929 contracts thus far today.
That number of contracts represents approximately 892,900 underlying shares, working out to a sizeable 106.8% of VMC's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 836,070 shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $120 strike call option expiring August 19, 2016 , with 2,495 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 249,500 underlying shares of VMC.

Below is a chart showing VMC's trailing twelve month trading history, with the $120 strike highlighted in orange:

And Procter & Gamble Co. (Symbol: PG) saw options trading volume of 62,378 contracts, representing approximately 6.2 million underlying shares or approximately 86% of PG's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 7.3 million shares.

Especially high volume was seen for the $87.50 strike call option expiring September 16, 2016 , with 12,236 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 1.2 million underlying shares of PG.
